This is the protocol for a review and there is no abstract. The objectives are as follows:, To assess the effects of oral isotretinoin in the treatment of severe, nodulocystic acne vulgaris, treatment-resistant acne vulgaris, and inflammatory, scarring acne. Specifically the review aims to:, (1) compare the efficacy of isotretinoin against other topical and systemic drug treatments and placebo, (2) collect data on the incidence of side effects associated with isotretinoin therapy (as number of participants reporting adverse events), (3) to determine whether the dose and duration of isotretinoin therapy have an impact on the adverse effects profile